thread.title: Durban ANC 'with students'

author: news24.com
title: Durban ANC 'with students'
text:
Durban - An ANC official who received a memorandum of demands from Durban #FeesMustFall demonstrators on Friday, said the ruling party supported the students.
Demonstrators, made up largely of University of KwaZulu Natal and Durban University of Technology students, marched from Curries Fountain to ANC headquarters in the city centre.
Speaking to News24 upon receiving the memorandum of demands, ANC official Bheki Ntuli commended demonstrators for not being violent.
"We have not heard any reports of damages despite the long march they had. We appreciate that. They proved they are indeed leaders of tomorrow and they know what they want.
